The distance to reach this co-ordinate is calculated using Manhattan distance, where the Manhattan distance between the points (x[i], y[i]) and (cx, cy) will be distance[i] = abs(x[i]  cx) + abs(y[i]  cy) . 

The corresponding cost for that path (x[i], y[i]) to (cx, cy) is calculated as price[i] * distance[i]

